@node "story"

                                          Page 3 of 9                                     



@{b}                               The story thus far!!@{ub}

              From the days of 8 color Icons into the 256 color icon era, there
              have been many an Eccelent@{b} NewIcon@{ub} in witch to download from AMINET,
              however, there seemed to be a problem for me, as I searched and searched for
              just the right breed of Icon that may suit my need, I have found nought!
              However, there is much to offer there as far as@{b} NewIcons@{ub} go and they
              may even just appear better than my own! (More than likely)! :-)
              But I hope that in the future of the RPG sceen will only then, be a@{b} NewIcon@{ub}
              set for the Meidevil RPG fans of the AMIGA! :-D

       I must say that there is also a lot of XEN icons avail that look very good, however, I like
       NewIcons, and I enjoy configureability.:)   SS-Amiga!  (SUPER SYSTEM)
                                        
                                                
@endnode
@node "port"

                                            Page 2 of 9

                                 @{b}IMPORTANT / Instalation@{ub}

            The Icons in this package are in@{b} NewIcon format@{ub}, so to Manipulate
            These@{b} images@{ub}, you must used the@{b} CopyNewIcon@{ub} Utility supplied with
            the NewIcons Package, but if you do not have the NewIcons Package
            installed, then you will just see small squares for the Icons. You@{b}
            MUST NOT COPY JUST THE ICON ITSELF@{ub} simply use the@{b} CopyNewIcon Utility.@{ub}
            As Phil said: "Think of these icons as a collection of images." If you
            are not using the NewIcon Package, or @{"  OS3.5  " link os}, theses Images are of
            no use to you. You can get the NewIcons package on Aminet:
               
                                    pub/aminet/util/wb/NewIcons46.lha
            
                                    Also check out the WWW at:
                                       
                                    @{b}http://www.amiganet.org/NewIcons@{ub}
                               
                                    WebMaster @{" Philip Vedovatti " link thank}

                                    The official NewIcons support site.
                                 For lots and lots of even better Icons! :)
@endnode
