@node "palette"

                                             Page 5 of 9                          


                                    @{b} The color Sceam!@{ub}
              

           The Icons in this Package use a 64 color color palette in with the first 32
           colors in the palette are the origonal NewIcons 32 color set! The second 32
           colors in the palette are used for some of the NewIcon (Treasure Box Drawers)
           and the Special WB Backdrops that are also included! Don't ask me why I did
           this cause I don't know Either! :-D You should have no problem if you use a
           128 color workbench. ( Sorry ) They should also look good with a 64 color
           Workbench as well, but not quite as good. All of the Items in this archive
           use the same palette, eccept the blue, cool baground, and the Cool Window,
           Windows Weive! So don't worry too much! ;-\

                                                                       
@endnode
@node "bonus"

                                           Page 4 of 9

                              @{b}  What do I get, you ask?...@{ub}

   Included with this package is A complete replacement set of@{b} NewIcon@{ub} Drawer Images for
   your Workbench, and Extra Drawers for some of the programs that you might have in some of your
   other Drives! Also, their is some Game Drawers for various RPG games for the Amiga, as well as
   Adventure Games. To Add to The RPG invirons, there is Also 6 pointers in the
  @{b}(Workbench/Prefs/Solid/Presets/(Pointer-Patterns@{ub} Drawer of this Package, 3 in LoRES and the
   same 3 in HiRES! There is also 6 WBPatterns in the same DIR: Think of this as a bonus plan! :-)
   Please note that these Pointers are Pointer Prefs. Simply...Open project. Don't try to@{b} Load Image@{ub}
   as you will not find them! Just select picture for the Patterns. The only thing you don't
   get, is the realy neet Border around the Icons in the@{" RPG_NIGrab.iff " link rpg_nigrab.iff/main}. :-)-
                                     
@endnode
@node "rights" 

                                          Page 7 of 9
          
                                                                                    FREE     :)         
                                      @{b}Distribution {ub}
            
           This NewIcon package is@{b} FREELY@{ub}  distributable, as long as the Archive stays
           intact and this Guide, is kept abound. (For the IMPORTANT part that is).
           This part should be familiar with most of you! :-) You can do what you want
           with the individual icons, I don't mind a bit. Make More! Send em to folks!
          
           Perhaps you will like these icons, perhaps not. If you do, and think that they should
           be improved, please, I encourage you to do so! I know they could be improved myself.
           I am working on it. If you do, and want to relese a similar package with this type of
           RPG style, please let @{" ME " link arther} know that you are doing this ok?:) That way, I can determine
           that these icons are realy a use of some sort and someone likes them! But I'm
           not realy a good artist and there are a lot of details left out in this package.
           I have decided that these icons are complete enough to Upload to Aminet, and I
           will continue to make them better. :) I have suplied a small Template to use
           when creating some of your own icons, with this pack. If you wish to view it now,
           then just click----->@{"  HERE  " link template.iff/main} If <--That snapshot looked like a four color pic,
           then make sure you are viewing this on your Main Workbench screen! Also, if this
           shot dosn't even load, then the pic has been moved to another location.

 	      @{b}FREE@{ub}    
