@node "os"

                                           Page 8 of 9

                                    @{b}If you are using os3.5:@{ub}



               If you want to conver these icons into genuine OS3.5 Icons, simply
               load them into the OS3.5 Icon Editor tool and save them. They will
               loose their NewIcon status and be converted into OS3.5 Icons. Most
               of you may be familiar with this, if not, thats how you do it!
               I am not currently using OS3.5. Haven't my CDROM yet! ( ALAS ).:(
               I do Have the CD though! But I know this because......Thanks Phil :)


@endnode
@node "arther"

                                           Page 9 of 9
                 
                                    @{b}Who am I, you ask?@{ub}

               Well, I am Kevin Hansen. This is my first upload, and I hope that this
               will not be the last. I have plans to make even more Icons in this style,
               providing that I get Enough E-Mail.:D That will encourage me to make
               more and more of this stuff! (As long as I can think..of somthing). I
               like drawing, however, I am not the best at it beleive me! :) I do it
               because its fun, and I havn't seen a Computer to date that allows the
               user, as well as a programer (witch I'm not:) to do Basicaly anything that
               he/she wants to do! You see a goal, go for it. The Amiga is a very
               special Computer, and it may be under appriciated by many, but the
               community is there, and thats what counts.
               
               Please, I encourage you to let me know the good and the bad about this
               Icon package, so don't be afraid to E-Mail me with comments/suggestions/
               bug reports:)/praises/latitude/longitude or just plain complaints!
               Anything that might be good and/or funny to hear! :-D I have a sense of
               humor, I can take it!
                                                       
